HEADWORD: Tree burial
<hw>Tree burial</hw>. <def>Disposal of the dead by placing the corpse
among the branches of a tree or in a hollow trunk, a practice among many
primitive peoples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

